<h1>Official releases</h1>
<p>If you want to use a stable, more or less tested version  of tel, then you should download an official release of tel. You can find them in the <a href="http://developer.berlios.de/project/showfiles.php?group_id=8132">download section</a> of BerliOS</p>

<h1>Subversion</h1>
<p>If you always want to use the latest version of tel, if you're not afraid of bugs and failures or if you're probably interested in the development process of tel, you can <a href="http://developer.berlios.de/svn/?group_id=8132">grap</a> the lastest bleeding edge code from the <a href="http://subversion.tigris.org/">subversion</a> repository.</p>